        "created_at": "2025-08-02T08:44:48.084Z",
        "cooked": "<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=5463785&amp;iNote=11987475\"><b>1969 Faiveley Morey St. Denis 1er Cru Les Genavri\u00e8res</b></a> - France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Nuits, Morey St. Denis 1er Cru (8/2/2025)<br>\nA good bottle but certainly in tertiary territory. Plenty of sous bois and some honeyed sweetness to the fruit profile. A wisp of smoke and some compost too. Silky of texture, decent volume and relaxed structural elements. It deepens with air and finishes with an iodine note. </li>\n</ul>\n<p>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/\">CellarTracker</a></p>",
